<div id="single" class="row">
  <div class="eight columns offset-by-two panel">
    <h1>Only the tweets you want, in your spreadsheet</h1>
    <h2>Twedar is a twitter research tool that allows you to create filtered searches that run 24/7, with Excel & Google docs export.</h2>
    <div class="splash-img">
      <%= image_tag "export-demo.png", :size => "130x130", :alt => "Watch multiple keywords" %>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <h3>Non-stop search, 24/7</h3>
    <p>Collect matching tweets continously, allowing you to collect large amounts of data for research even on niche terms.</p>

    <h3>Smart filtering</h3>
    <p>Avoid boring and time consuming filtering - teach our system what you're interested in. Simply click 'yes' and 'no' on tweets that do or don't interest you and our system does the rest.</p>


    <h3>Instant feedback</h3>
    <p>See which tweets you're capturing in real time. Get started in seconds.</p>

    <h3>Export</h3>
    <p>Export as CSV files, understood by Excel, SPSS, R and a host of other industry standard research tools.</p>

    <div class="row signup-button">
      <div class="eight columns offset-by-two">
        <h4>Make Twitter work for you with Twedar</h4>
        <a href="/auth/twitter" class="button nice radius blue large">Sign in with Twitter</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

